19 int estimator::getClosestTracker(const measurement meas) // Nearest neighbour approach
20 {
21 double dist = std::numeric_limits<float>::infinity();
22 int closest = 0; // Maybe init this -1?
23 double temp = 0;
24 for(int i = 0; i < 10; i++)
25 {
26 temp = hypot(trackers_[i].mean_(0) - meas.x_, trackers_[i].mean_(1) - meas.y_);
27 if(temp < dist)
28 {
29 dist = temp;
30 closest = i;
31 }
32 }
33 return closest;
34 }

36 std::map<int, std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>> estimator::getMatchesInGate(double PD)
37 {
38 // Two questions comes to mind
39 // Is 2d position enough?
40 // How about adding velocities and-or volume info?
41 double dist_sq = 0;
42 double pos_dist = 0;
43 double gate_eps = 1;
44 Eigen::VectorXd innovation(7), meas_eig(7);
45 Eigen::MatrixXd sk_inv2(2,2);
46 std::vector<std::pair<int,double>> gated_measurements;
47 std::map<int, std::vector<std::pair<int, double>>> matches;
48 std::pair<int ,double> temp_p;
49 for(int i = 0; i < trackers_.size(); i++)
50 {
51 gated_measurements.clear();
52 kalman_filter::kalmanFilter track = trackers_[i]; // Getting a copy of tracker object
53 track.prediction(); // Just updating the copy, not the element itself...
54 sk_inv2 = track.cov_p_.block<2,2>(1,1).inverse();
55 uviz_.visualizeTwo2DGates(track.mean_p_(0), track.mean_p_(1), sk_inv2, 5, i);
56 for(int j = 0 ; j < measurements_.size(); j++)
57 {
58 meas_eig = common::toEigen(measurements_[j]);
59 innovation = meas_eig - track.mean_p_;
60 dist_sq = innovation.transpose() * track.cov_p_.inverse() * innovation; // Covariance scales down the dimensions
61 // We can compute and visualize 2d elipsoids here.
62 pos_dist = (innovation.head(2).transpose() * sk_inv2 *innovation.head(2));
63 ROS_INFO("Tracker %d , meas %i, dist %.2f, pose_dist %.2f",i,j,sqrt(dist_sq),sqrt(pos_dist));
64 if(dist_sq < gate_eps) //
65 {
66 double gauss_val = PD * common::getGaussianValue(sk_inv2, innovation.head(2)); //Just using 2d values here...
67 gated_measurements.push_back(std::make_pair(j, gauss_val));
68 }
69 }
70 matches[i] = gated_measurements; // Assign the gated measurements to track.
71 }
72 return matches;
73 }

75 bool estimator::checkMatchValidity(std::vector<std::pair<int,double>> candidates, double& normalizer)
76 {
77 // Calculates normalizer for weights
78 // Checks if correspondences is more probable than no match.
79 double base(0.1); // 1-PD for 0;
80 double match_prob(0);
81 for(auto pair : candidates)
82 {
83 match_prob += pair.second;
84 }
85 normalizer = 1.0/(base+match_prob);
86 ROS_INFO("No match %.2f, match %.2f",base,match_prob);
87 return (match_prob>base); //
88 }
